00:20:45,980 --> 00:20:47,809
It's what gives all matter mass.

261
00:20:47,810 --> 00:20:49,939
The thing without which we could not exist.

262
00:20:49,940 --> 00:20:52,819
You're talking about the moment of creation.

263
00:20:52,820 --> 00:20:54,750
Yes. In a way, I am.

264
00:20:55,530 --> 00:20:57,739
The antimatter is suspended there...

265
00:20:57,740 --> 00:21:01,489
...in an airtight nanocomposite shell with
electromagnets in each end.

266
00:21:01,490 --> 00:21:04,959
If it were to fall out of suspension
and come in contact with matter...

267
00:21:04,960 --> 00:21:07,999
...say, the bottom of the canister,
the two opposing forces...

268
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:10,249
...would annihilate one another violently.

269
00:21:10,250 --> 00:21:12,709
And what might cause it to
fall out of suspension?

270
