00:24:41,420 --> 00:24:44,379
One every hour at 8,9,10 and 11.

332
00:24:44,380 --> 00:24:47,350
Then the device explodes at midnight.

333
00:24:47,720 --> 00:24:51,099
If we can figure out the first church
and get there before he does...

334
00:24:51,100 --> 00:24:54,389
...maybe we can stop it.
But I can't find the start of the path...

335
00:24:54,390 --> 00:24:56,610
...until I get into the archives.

336
00:24:57,270 --> 00:24:59,149
Even if I wanted to help you...

337
00:24:59,150 --> 00:25:01,819
...access to the archives is
only by written decree...

338
00:25:01,820 --> 00:25:04,859
...by the curator
and the Board of Vatican Librarians.

339
00:25:04,860 --> 00:25:06,699
Or by papal mandate.

340
00:25:06,700 --> 00:25:10,840
Yes, but as you no doubt have heard,
the Holy Father is dead.

341
00:25:11,370 --> 00:25:12,829
What about il camerlengo?

342
00:25:12,830 --> 00:25:16,329
The camerlengo is just a priest here,
the former pope's chamberlain.

343
00:25:16,330 --> 00:25:20,640
Doesn't the power of the Holy See
rest in him during tempe sede vacante?

344
00:25:28,300 --> 00:25:31,480
Fellas, you called me.

345
00:25:32,600 --> 00:25:34,429
His Holiness once told me a pope...

346
00:25:34,430 --> 00:25:38,229
...was a man torn between
the real world and the divine.

347
00:25:38,230 --> 00:25:41,700
It seems the real world is upon us tonight.

348
00:25:42,440 --> 00:25:46,370
I'm familiar with Illuminati lore
and the legend of the brandings.

349
00:25:46,490 --> 00:25:49,949
La purga is a dark stain
on this Church's history.

350
00:25:49,950 --> 00:25:53,290
I'm not surprised this ghost
has returned to haunt us.

351
00:25:55,200 --> 00:25:58,749
Comandante, have you begun
the search for this explosive device?

352
00:25:58,750 --> 00:26:00,629
Of course, but it could be anywhere.

353
00:26:00,630 --> 00:26:02,169
My primary concern at the moment

354
00:26:02,170 --> 00:26:03,709
is the safety of the cardinals.

355
00:26:03,710 --> 00:26:05,879
The Sistine Chapel is a fortress.

356
00:26:05,880 --> 00:26:07,979
as long as the cardinals are in conclave,

357
00:26:07,980 --> 00:26:08,759
your securety concerns...

358
00:26:08,760 --> 00:26:10,169
...are at a minimum.

359
00:26:10,170 --> 00:26:11,469
Devote as many of your resources-

360
00:26:11,470 --> 00:26:13,849
If you're about to suggest
a naked-eye search...

361
00:26:13,850 --> 00:26:15,539
...of the entire Vatican City,

362
00:26:15,540 --> 00:26:17,389
I will tell you we do not have the people.

363
00:26:17,390 --> 00:26:19,309
Though I'm not His Holiness,

364
00:26:19,310 --> 00:26:20,559
when you are addressing me...

365
00:26:20,560 --> 00:26:23,280
...you are addressing this office.
Do you understand?

366
00:26:25,280 --> 00:26:26,620
Yes, Father.

367
00:26:26,900 --> 00:26:28,950
Good.

368
00:26:29,490 --> 00:26:31,529
You said the image on the screen

369
00:26:31,530 --> 00:26:33,739
was illuminated by artificail light.

370
00:26:33,740 --> 00:26:36,039
Might I suggest methodically
cutting power...

371
00:26:36,040 --> 00:26:38,329
...to various sections of the city.

372
00:26:38,330 --> 00:26:41,079
When the image goes dark,
you'll have a specific idea...

373
00:26:41,080 --> 00:26:43,470
...of the camera's location.

374
00:26:46,590 --> 00:26:50,219
Dr. Vetra, besides yourself
and your research partner...

375
00:26:50,220 --> 00:26:53,940
...who else knew about this
antimatter project?

376
00:26:54,060 --> 00:26:56,719
No one but the research ream.

377
00:26:56,720 --> 00:26:58,599
This project was strictly confidential.

378
00:26:58,600 --> 00:27:00,689
But Silvano kept detailed journals.

379
00:27:00,690 --> 00:27:02,280
If he told anyone else...

380
00:27:02,560 --> 00:27:05,269
...about what we were doing,
he would have made a note.

381
00:27:05,270 --> 00:27:06,859
Do you have these journals?

382
00:27:06,860 --> 00:27:09,569
I can have them flown here from
Geneva in an hour.

383
00:27:09,570 --> 00:27:11,540
Please.

384
00:27:12,620 --> 00:27:14,250
Professor Langdon.

385
00:27:25,130 --> 00:27:28,309
Mr. Langdon, you are correct that

386
00:27:28,310 --> 00:27:31,060
I may grant you access to the archives.

387
00:27:32,890 --> 00:27:34,799
Thank you, Padre.

388
00:27:34,800 --> 00:27:38,860
I said that you were correct that I may,
not that I will.

389
00:27:39,730 --> 00:27:43,030
Christianity's most sacred codices
are in that archive.

390
00:27:44,230 --> 00:27:47,819
Given your recent entanglement
with the Church...

391
00:27:47,820 --> 00:27:50,319
...there is a question I'd like to
ask you first...

392
00:27:50,320 --> 00:27:53,080
...in the office of His Holiness.

393
00:28:00,580 --> 00:28:02,550
Do you believe in God, sir?

394
00:28:06,040 --> 00:28:09,589
Father, I simply believe that religion-

395
00:28:09,590 --> 00:28:13,259
I did not ask if you believe what
man says about God.

396
00:28:13,260 --> 00:28:15,390
I asked if you believe in God

397
00:28:18,060 --> 00:28:20,070
I'm an academic.

398
00:28:20,890 --> 00:28:24,099
My minds tells me I will never...

399
00:28:24,100 --> 00:28:25,860
...understand God.

400
00:28:26,610 --> 00:28:28,490
And your heart?

401
00:28:31,030 --> 00:28:33,620
Tells me I'm not meant to.

402
00:28:34,780 --> 00:28:36,619
Faith is a gift...

403
00:28:36,620 --> 00:28:39,080
...that I have yet to receive.

404
00:28:45,290 --> 00:28:48,180
Be delicate with our treasures.

405
00:28:54,300 --> 00:28:55,629
The archives are this way.

406
00:28:55,630 --> 00:28:57,850
Professor Langdon.

407
00:28:58,640 --> 00:29:00,049
If this path really leads to

408
00:29:00,050 --> 00:29:01,969
the Church of Illumination...

409
00:29:01,970 --> 00:29:04,479
...that way may be where they've
hidden the antimatter.

410
00:29:04,480 --> 00:29:06,439
"A shining star at the end of the path. "

411
00:29:06,440 --> 00:29:07,649
Follow the path.

412
00:29:07,650 --> 00:29:09,219
We may find the canister.

413
00:29:09,220 --> 00:29:10,649
Can you deactivate the device?

414
00:29:10,650 --> 00:29:12,149
I can change the batteries...

415
00:29:12,150 --> 00:29:14,569
...as long as we have more than
five minutes.

416
00:29:14,570 --> 00:29:16,089
That would give us another 24 hours

417
00:29:16,090 --> 00:29:18,120
to get it safely back to CERN.

418
00:29:20,910 --> 00:29:22,119
Robert Langdon

419
00:29:22,120 --> 00:29:23,949
Vittoria Vetra.

420
00:29:23,950 --> 00:29:27,629
Are you really a symbologist,
or was he mocking you?

421
00:29:27,630 --> 00:29:29,959
Well, both. You're a physicist?

422
00:29:29,960 --> 00:29:31,169
Bio-entanglement physics.

423
00:29:31,170 --> 00:29:33,339
Interconnectivity of life system.

424
00:29:33,340 --> 00:29:34,799
Okay.

425
00:29:34,800 --> 00:29:38,009
Your project, it was geared
towards energy research?

426
00:29:38,010 --> 00:29:39,349
Eventually, yes.

427
00:29:39,350 --> 00:29:40,759
One speck of antimatter

428
00:29:40,760 --> 00:29:43,599
could power an entire city for a month.

429
00:29:43,600 --> 00:29:46,240
Or tonight, I guess, destroy one.

