01:51:05,270 --> 01:51:07,360
We only have 19 minutes

1295
01:51:11,400 --> 01:51:13,319
Here. He's...

1296
01:51:13,320 --> 01:51:15,489
get the helicopter for the older cardinals.

1297
01:51:15,490 --> 01:51:17,160
Yes, sir.

1298
01:51:29,880 --> 01:51:31,379
Robert?

1299
01:51:31,380 --> 01:51:33,259
The brand, the symbol,

1300
01:51:33,260 --> 01:51:34,970
could it have another meaning?

1301
01:51:40,680 --> 01:51:43,730
Crossed keys, but those were upside down.

1302
01:51:44,060 --> 01:51:45,860
St. Peter.

1303
01:51:46,770 --> 01:51:48,820
The first pope...

1304
01:51:49,400 --> 01:51:51,269
...was crucified upside down.

1305
01:51:51,270 --> 01:51:53,979
- On Vatican Hill.
- A few hundred feet below us.

1306
01:51:53,980 --> 01:51:55,489
Necropolis. City of the dead.

1307
01:51:55,490 --> 01:51:58,069
"Upon this rock, I will build my church. "

1308
01:51:58,070 --> 01:52:01,250
"Or bring it down upon itself. "

1309
01:52:01,830 --> 01:52:05,130
The bomb. It's in St. Peter's tomb.

1310
01:52:20,010 --> 01:52:21,679
The grid is still cycling.

1311
01:52:21,680 --> 01:52:24,360
The power to this section must be down.

1312
01:53:22,400 --> 01:53:25,540
It must be here. It must be.

1313
01:53:37,600 --> 01:53:38,780
Don't touch it.

1314
01:53:39,600 --> 01:53:41,990
We have seven minutes.

1315
01:53:47,150 --> 01:53:49,790
Robert, hold this.

1316
01:54:30,570 --> 01:54:32,739
It's cold down here, isn't it?

1317
01:54:32,740 --> 01:54:34,370
What's wrong?

1318
01:54:34,660 --> 01:54:37,330
Cold decreases battery life

1319
01:54:39,160 --> 01:54:41,300
We may have less than five minutes.

1320
01:54:41,660 --> 01:54:43,169
So?

1321
01:54:43,170 --> 01:54:45,919
If I pull the power with less
than five minutes...

1322
01:54:45,920 --> 01:54:48,760
...the residual charge won't
hold suspension.

1323
01:54:50,340 --> 01:54:53,469
We should leave it here
and get clear if we can.

1324
01:54:53,470 --> 01:54:55,849
- At least down here the damage-
- No!

1325
01:54:55,850 --> 01:54:58,310
- No. Wait!
- Father!

1326
01:55:00,430 --> 01:55:02,519
We are live here at St. Peter's Square...

1327
01:55:02,520 --> 01:55:06,189
where, despite a bomb threat,
and an order of evacuation...

1328
01:55:06,190 --> 01:55:09,939
...the crowd is actually growing in size
As we await an official...

1329
01:55:09,940 --> 01:55:12,029
...announcement from
the Vatican spokesman...

1330
01:55:12,030 --> 01:55:14,199
...as to the exact nature of the threat...

1331
01:55:14,200 --> 01:55:18,080
...and whether or not they
are treating it as a credible danger.

1332
01:55:25,420 --> 01:55:26,930
This way.

1333
01:55:59,450 --> 01:56:01,670
A bomb?

1334
01:56:06,080 --> 01:56:10,220
Roberto, this is an emergency.
I'll take her up alone.

1335
01:56:14,010 --> 01:56:16,060
He's got clearance.

1336
01:56:40,990 --> 01:56:43,210
Oh, my God.

1337
01:58:44,450 --> 01:58:46,120
Get down!

1338
02:01:38,620 --> 02:01:40,999
Cardinal Strauss?

1339
02:01:41,000 --> 02:01:45,089
It was the Camerlengo.
He has saved us all.

1340
02:01:45,090 --> 02:01:49,350
He has saved the Church
and he's still alive.

1341
02:01:50,010 --> 02:01:51,890
Praise God. Praise God.

1342
02:01:57,350 --> 02:01:58,929
He is alive.

1343
02:01:58,930 --> 02:02:02,740
He sacrificed himself for all of us.

1344
02:02:30,510 --> 02:02:34,639
You know the worst thing
we thought would happen?

1345
02:02:34,640 --> 02:02:38,940
Was that our work would fall into
the hands of the energy companies.

1346
02:02:40,850 --> 02:02:43,450
We thought we could change the world.

1347
02:02:43,690 --> 02:02:45,059
So naive.

1348
02:02:45,060 --> 02:02:48,859
No, not naive.

1349
02:02:48,860 --> 02:02:50,859
Innocent, maybe.

1350
02:02:50,860 --> 02:02:53,460
But it's not a crime.

1351
02:02:54,530 --> 02:02:56,960
I'm not so sure.

1352
02:02:58,240 --> 02:03:01,050
Go back to work.

1353
02:03:01,660 --> 02:03:04,050
Change the world.

1354
02:03:22,680 --> 02:03:25,899
A gift, uh, you understand?

1355
02:03:25,900 --> 02:03:28,899
Let's say for Catholics everywhere.

1356
02:03:28,900 --> 02:03:32,649
The Carmerlengo's age shouldn't
reach the decision.

1357
02:03:32,650 --> 02:03:35,029
Signori

1358
02:03:35,030 --> 02:03:38,869
you are no doubt aware that the Holy Law of
that man is ineligible for election to the papacy.

1359
02:03:38,870 --> 02:03:40,909
He's not a cardinal. He's a priest.

1360
02:03:40,910 --> 02:03:42,789
He's of insufficient age.

1361
02:03:42,790 --> 02:03:46,079
Or maybe there's a way we could
consider the possibility.

1362
02:03:46,080 --> 02:03:50,879
I am sorry. The protocols of conclave
are not subject to modification.

1363
02:03:50,880 --> 02:03:52,969
I will not call a ballot on this matter.

1364
02:03:52,970 --> 02:03:55,969
But, signore, you would not hold a ballot.

1365
02:03:55,970 --> 02:03:57,429
Surely, you remember?

1366
02:03:57,430 --> 02:04:00,389
You gave up your post as Great Elector.

1367
02:04:00,390 --> 02:04:02,719
They are singing at St. Peter's Square.

1368
02:04:02,720 --> 02:04:05,599
Now, what happened here tonight
transcends our laws.

1369
02:04:05,600 --> 02:04:06,809
Has it?

1370
02:04:06,810 --> 02:04:10,109
Is it God's will that we give
ourselves over to frenzy?

1371
02:04:10,110 --> 02:04:11,899
Discard the rules of the Church?

1372
02:04:11,900 --> 02:04:14,790
Perhaps we need not discard them.

1373
02:04:15,280 --> 02:04:21,369
Signori, I am thinking now of Romano
Pontifici Eligendo numero 60...

1374
02:04:21,370 --> 02:04:23,460
- Acclamation by Adoration.
- Exactly, signore. Exactly.

1375
02:04:24,580 --> 02:04:27,829
Yes. If the Holy Spirit speaks through us...

1376
02:04:27,830 --> 02:04:30,379
and we call a man's name out loud...

1377
02:04:30,380 --> 02:04:33,169
That is election by adoration.

1378
02:04:33,170 --> 02:04:35,759
He's God's choice.

1379
02:04:35,760 --> 02:04:40,929
Yes. And the candidate need only be an
ordained member of the clergy...

1380
02:04:40,930 --> 02:04:45,940
present in the Sistine Chapel at
the moment of his election.

1381
02:04:53,690 --> 02:04:55,490
I think we havn't certain...

1382
02:05:18,880 --> 02:05:20,390
Signor Camerlengo?

1383
02:05:20,720 --> 02:05:21,929
Yes?

1384
02:05:21,930 --> 02:05:26,139
The cardinals ask you to join them in
conclave as soon as possible.

1385
02:05:26,140 --> 02:05:27,519
Me?

1386
02:05:27,520 --> 02:05:29,900
Yes, Padre.

1387
02:05:52,170 --> 02:05:53,499
What are you doing?

1388
02:05:53,500 --> 02:05:56,890
Silvano's journals. I want them back.

1389
02:06:21,030 --> 02:06:23,330
Richter said...

1390
02:06:24,200 --> 02:06:26,369
His Holiness suffered from seizures...

1391
02:06:26,370 --> 02:06:29,000
and steps were taken...

1392
02:06:29,830 --> 02:06:31,800
for safety.

1393
02:06:35,880 --> 02:06:39,180
He made sure he was watched he said.

1394
02:06:40,380 --> 02:06:44,350
What if he were trying to give
me this key?

1395
02:06:44,720 --> 02:06:47,259
That's the Papal office.

1396
02:06:47,260 --> 02:06:49,309
If the Pope was worried about seizures,

1397
02:06:49,310 --> 02:06:52,559
he must've had Richter install cameras
without telling anyone.

1398
02:06:52,560 --> 02:06:55,530
To keep an eye on him for his safety.

1399
02:06:57,070 --> 02:06:59,120
Maybe it records.

1400
02:07:09,830 --> 02:07:11,709
I read the journals, Patrick.

1401
02:07:11,710 --> 02:07:14,459
The scientist kept journals. So?

1402
02:07:14,460 --> 02:07:16,470
You figure prominently in them.

1403
02:07:16,880 --> 02:07:18,089
Really?

1404
02:07:18,090 --> 02:07:22,810
The Devoli wasn't just a physicist.
He was also a Catholic priest.

1405
02:07:23,090 --> 02:07:27,259
As such, he was deeply conflicted
about the implications of his work

1406
02:07:27,260 --> 02:07:29,929
and in need of spiritual guidance.

1407
02:07:29,930 --> 02:07:32,070
Like Galileo.

1408
02:07:32,730 --> 02:07:36,149
About a month ago...
he requested an audience with the Pope.

1409
02:07:36,150 --> 02:07:38,019
But you know that.

1410
02:07:38,020 --> 02:07:41,439
You soon granted the audience
and you were also present during it.

1411
02:07:41,440 --> 02:07:44,609
The 'God Particle'.

1412
02:07:44,610 --> 02:07:46,619
To actually claim an act of creation.
The blasphemy. The arrogance.

1413
02:07:46,620 --> 02:07:49,369
The Holy Father didn't see it like that.

1414
02:07:49,370 --> 02:07:51,449
He urged him to go public.

1415
02:07:51,450 --> 02:07:53,539
His Holiness thought that the discovery

1416
02:07:53,540 --> 02:07:57,749
could actually scientifically prove
the existence of a divine power.

1417
02:07:57,750 --> 02:08:00,919
And begin to bridge the gap
between science and religion.

1418
02:08:00,920 --> 02:08:03,799
His work was not religious.
It was sacrilegious.

1419
02:08:03,800 --> 02:08:08,980
But you... You saw the pope's position
as a softening of church law.

1420
02:08:09,470 --> 02:08:13,400
As an old man's weakness.
Your father's weakness.

1421
02:08:13,770 --> 02:08:15,599
Your father's weakness.

1422
02:08:15,600 --> 02:08:19,649
He raised me to protect this Church...
even from within.

1423
02:08:19,650 --> 02:08:23,950
Then you conjured up an old
enemy from the past. The Illuminati.

1424
02:08:25,820 --> 02:08:30,119
You found the ancient brands in the papal
vaults and put them to use...

1425
02:08:30,120 --> 02:08:31,329
to spread fear!

1426
02:08:31,330 --> 02:08:33,909
The Cardinals are men of belief.

1427
02:08:33,910 --> 02:08:37,579
Right now,
their belief in evil is uniting them.

1428
02:08:37,580 --> 02:08:40,919
The entire Catholic world
will be united by this attack.

1429
02:08:40,920 --> 02:08:43,140
There is no attack.

1430
02:08:43,840 --> 02:08:46,799
You're trying to convince
the Cardinals they're in a war...

1431
02:08:46,800 --> 02:08:49,049
so they will choose a warrior to lead them.

1432
02:08:49,050 --> 02:08:50,349
We are at war.

1433
02:08:50,350 --> 02:08:52,469
We're weak when we should be strong.

1434
02:08:52,470 --> 02:08:56,479
If science is allowed to claim
the power of creation...

1435
02:08:56,480 --> 02:08:58,349
what is left for God?

1436
02:08:58,350 --> 02:09:00,320
It didn't work, Patrick.

1437
02:09:01,520 --> 02:09:05,200
- It isn't finished.
- Oh, yes, it's finished.

1438
02:09:06,110 --> 02:09:08,330
It's finished.

1439
02:09:09,030 --> 02:09:12,029
I've shown the journals to Father Simeon.

1440
02:09:12,030 --> 02:09:14,489
The moment the doors to the Conclave open...

1441
02:09:14,490 --> 02:09:17,710
he will tell the Cardinals what you've done.

1442
02:09:17,960 --> 02:09:20,760
I was planning on doing this alone.

1443
02:09:23,380 --> 02:09:25,100
Put it down.

1444
02:09:27,470 --> 02:09:30,389
But, perhaps, it's better that you're here.

1445
02:09:30,390 --> 02:09:31,810
Put it down.

1446
02:09:33,350 --> 02:09:35,440
Put it away.

1447
02:09:47,490 --> 02:09:50,790
Help. He's the one. He's got a gun.

1448
02:09:54,330 --> 02:09:56,749
- Illuminatus.
- You bastard.

1449
02:09:56,750 --> 02:09:59,590
- Illuminatus!
- You bastard!

1450
02:10:03,600 --> 02:10:05,650
Padre.

1451
02:10:14,680 --> 02:10:17,980
And get the helicopter
for the older cardinals, right?

1452
02:11:08,940 --> 02:11:12,200
I've been summoned
by the College of Cardinals.

1453
02:12:25,350 --> 02:12:26,809
Gently.

1454
02:12:26,810 --> 02:12:31,350
But within our walls.

1455
02:12:40,940 --> 02:12:43,130
He's on your side.

1456
02:13:32,060 --> 02:13:36,080
Father,
into their hands I commend my spirit.

1457
02:14:29,490 --> 02:14:31,329
Church sources now confirm that

1458
02:14:31,330 --> 02:14:33,749
Carmelengo,Father Patrick McKenna

1459
02:14:33,750 --> 02:14:38,709
has died of internal injuries
sustained in his heroic fall...

1460
02:14:38,710 --> 02:14:40,999
The Catholic church thanks Camerlengo

1461
02:14:41,000 --> 02:14:45,169
for his selfless act
and demands his immediate canonization.

1462
02:14:45,170 --> 02:14:49,009
The Vatican has also confirmed
the deaths of three Cardinals

1463
02:14:49,010 --> 02:14:51,679
and the fire in the Santa Maria
della Vittoria.

1464
02:14:51,680 --> 02:14:54,349
As we await the appearance of the new Holy Father

1465
02:14:54,350 --> 02:14:56,139
Cardinal Baggia of Italy...

1466
02:14:56,140 --> 02:14:59,899
one of the four original Preferiti...

1467
02:14:59,900 --> 02:15:02,229
who, despite terrorist
attempts at disruption...

1468
02:15:02,230 --> 02:15:04,819
seems to have been selected in one of
the swiftest and smoothest conclaves

1469
02:15:04,820 --> 02:15:06,910
in modern church history.

1470
02:15:13,580 --> 02:15:15,800
Professor Langdon? Please.

1471
02:15:32,930 --> 02:15:36,429
A token of thanks from His Holiness...

1472
02:15:36,430 --> 02:15:39,820
and from his new Camerlengo.

1473
02:15:40,770 --> 02:15:43,729
We are grateful you saved his life.

1474
02:15:43,730 --> 02:15:47,149
And it's our understanding
that you require this text...

1475
02:15:47,150 --> 02:15:49,500
to complete your scholary work.

1476
02:15:51,240 --> 02:15:54,529
We ask only that in your last
grand testament...

1477
02:15:54,530 --> 02:15:56,989
you ensure

1478
02:15:56,990 --> 02:15:59,210
it finds its way home.

1479
02:16:01,670 --> 02:16:02,919
Of course.

1480
02:16:02,920 --> 02:16:05,289
And when you write of us...

1481
02:16:05,290 --> 02:16:08,259
and you will write of us...

1482
02:16:08,260 --> 02:16:10,719
may I ask one thing?

1483
02:16:10,720 --> 02:16:12,600
Do so gently.

1484
02:16:14,800 --> 02:16:16,469
I'll try.

1485
02:16:16,470 --> 02:16:18,610
Religion is flawed...

1486
02:16:18,980 --> 02:16:21,979
but only because man is flawed.

1487
02:16:21,980 --> 02:16:25,700
All men, including this one.

1488
02:16:40,000 --> 02:16:42,130
He chose the name Luke.

1489
02:16:44,790 --> 02:16:47,800
There's been many Marks and Johns.

1490
02:16:49,170 --> 02:16:51,060
Never a Luke.

1491
02:16:51,470 --> 02:16:53,140
It said he was a doctor.

1492
02:16:54,180 --> 02:16:58,349
It's quite a message.
Science and faith, all in one.

1493
02:16:58,350 --> 02:17:00,270
The world is in need of both.

1494
02:17:02,850 --> 02:17:05,570
You'll counsel him wisely.

1495
02:17:05,610 --> 02:17:09,490
I'm an old man. I'll counsel him briefly.

1496
02:17:14,820 --> 02:17:17,170
Mr. Langdon.

1497
02:17:22,040 --> 02:17:26,970
Thanks be to God for sending
someone to protect this church.

1498
02:17:30,880 --> 02:17:33,719
I don't believe He sent me, Father.

1499
02:17:33,720 --> 02:17:36,179
Oh, my son.

1500
02:17:36,180 --> 02:17:38,520
Of course He did.

